citeinfo.title: School Facilities (Public and Private) in Florida - 2017

descript.abstract: This dataset contains 2017 Private and Public School Information for the State of Florida. It is a combination of schools and educational facility addresses from various sources, including the Florida Department of Education, the U.S. Department of Education National Center for Education Statistics, and other sources listed below. The data contains selected fields denoting the physical address, school number, district, and contact information for schools located in Florida. This data is meant to be used for planning purposes only and is not intended to represent a 100% inventory of schools. School locations that have been verified are marked with the letter V in the FLAG field. This dataset is an update to the GC_SCHOOLS_MAY12 layer. This layer corresponds to the schools boundary layer GC_SCHOOLSBND_SEP17 available through FGDL.
descript.purpose: The data was created to serve as base information for use in GIS systems for a variety of planning and analytical purposes.
descript.supplinf:
Master School Identification File Background and Use The Master School Identification (MSID) file is maintained by the Department of Education (DOE) to ensure the Department provides accurate identification and directory information on each Florida public school in the state. This file contains information for all public PK-12 schools as well as for adult and vocational-technical schools operated by district school boards. Information from this file is used for direct communication to the schools as well as for reporting data for each school. The Master School Identification file is used to edit all records submitted to the Department's Student, Staff and Finance Automated Data Base Systems. The MSID provides the universe for accountability reporting, including annual school grades and adequate yearly progress calculations. It is the basis for reporting to the U.S. Department of Education (USDE) via the Common Core of Data and Education Data Exchange Network (EDEN) reporting systems. The federally-assigned identification numbers, which are required for certain grant applications and for assignment of E-rate funds, are provided to the Florida DOE the year following submission of new school information to the USDE.
Accessing the File Appendix A provides a list of the elements contained in the Master School Identification file. MSID information for each Florida public school is available on the web at: http://doeweb-prd.doe.state.fl.us/EDS/MasterSchoolID. The data are presented in three sections: 1) addresses, 2) administration and 3) accountability. Three ways are provided for the user to look up a school: 1) by the school name, 2) by the district in which the school is located and 3) by the city/town in which the school is located.
School Type School Type is an indication of the level of instruction offered at the school. The School Type is derived directly from the Grade Code reported for the school. Elementary Schools: Schools providing instruction at one or more grade levels from PK through grade 5. May include schools serving grade 6 if also serving one or more grades PK through 5 (e.g., a K-6 school). Middle/Junior High Schools: Schools providing instruction in middle school configurations (grades 6-8) and junior high school configurations (grades 7-9). Can also include schools serving a single grade in the 6-8 range (e.g., a 6th grade center). Senior High Schools: Schools providing instruction at one or more grade levels from 9 to 12. Includes regular high schools and 9th grade centers. Combination Elementary and Secondary Schools: Schools providing instruction in grade groupings that include more than one of the categories described above (e.g., PK-8, 6-12, K-12, etc.). Adult Schools: Schools providing adult education instruction.
FDOE Public Schools are from the Master School ID file, Public schools are from the 2016-2017 school year. http://doeweb-prd.doe.state.fl.us/EDS/MasterSchoolID
FDOE K-12 Private Schools are from the Florida Department of Education K-12 Private Schools Annual Survey, Private schools are from the 2014-2015 school year. http://www.floridaschoolchoice.org/information/PrivateSchoolDirectory/Default.aspx
****************************************************
The Common Core of Data (CCD) is a program of the U.S. Department of Education's National Center for Education Statistics that annually collects fiscal and non-fiscal data about all public schools, public school districts and state education agencies in the United States. The data are supplied by state education agency officials and include information that describes schools and school districts, including name, address, and phone number; descriptive information about students and staff, including demographics; and fiscal data, including revenues and current expenditures.
http://nces.ed.gov/ccd/address.asp
NCES public school data is gathered by CCD (Common Core of Data), Public school data is from the 2014-2015 school year http://nces.ed.gov/ccd/
NCES private school data is gathered by PSS (Private School Universe Survey), Private school data is from the 2013-2014 school year.
NCES college data is gathered by IPEDS, College data is from the 2015-2016 school year.

procstep.procdesc:
The GeoPlan Center performed the following steps in order to create the 2008 statewide schools data layer.
68 Different Sources Comprise the Schools Dataset.
The following Sources were either reprojected to the FGDL Albers NAD83 HPGN map projection or if no spatial data existed they were geocoded to a statewide 2007 TeleAtlas Streets dataset. For downloaded county and district wide polygon layers the label points were created and then used for each facility.
Once the point sources were created via geocoding or reprojected existing point data they were merged into one statewide layer.
Record (facility) duplications were removed by manually viewing and editing the statewide layer's attribute table for each of the 67 counties. Where record duplication existed source information of previously corrected FDOT Districts and Regional Planning Council data took preference followed by, County data, and finally geocoded data.
Finally the FDOE state identification number and the NCES federal identification numbers were added for each facility with such an id. Next a table join was performed for each table (FDOE and NCES) to the master statewide shapefile. Un-used or duplicate fields were deleted.

---------------------------------------------------------------------- Spatial updates: -Converted downloaded Excel tables to DBF table in spatial database
-Compared/investigated records in this table that were not in gc_schools_jul08.shp. Populated a h_check field by marking them as: 0= add to gc_schools_may12 and 1= already reside in the gc_schools_jul08 dataset, 3= investigate further.
-Flag field: -V = verified. Verified means that the point has been visually checked, point is over building, and that the record was also found in the MSID
-NV = not verified. Not verified means that unable to verify the school and/or its location
-Duplicates were marked as duplicate and were later deleted
-If the point was new, the point was moved from the geocoded generated spot, the SCORE field was populated with '0', SIDE was populated with '*', and MATCH_ADRESS was populated as blank.
-A duplicate point of all superintendent offices was created and the name was calculated as "**** COUNTY STUDENT SERVICES/ MIGRANT/VIRTUAL PROGRAM/ MCKAY SCHOLARSHIP/ HOMEBOUND PROGRAM" and its FEDERAL_ID was calculated as the migrant program ID when available.
---------------------------------------------------------------------- Attribute table updates:
-Cleaned up city, county, and address fields in updated layer, ex. Ft. Myers became FORT MYERS. Replaced sch with school when found.
-COMMENT field records that were previously populated were given parentheses to separate previous update from current update
-PARCEL_ID was updated for points without an ID by identifying the parcel boundary that the point was within and copying LINK field from statewide_parcels10.shp to PARCEL_ID
-LAT_DD, LONG_DD were updated by calculating geometry tool
-USNG_FL_1K was updated through a spatial join
-For added records, source updated to GEOPLAN
-FGDLAQDATE and UPDATE_DAY were updated
-For public schools (OP_CLASS = 'PUBLIC'): -Joined gc_schools_may12.shp and MSID_all_schools.dbf based on STATE_ID -Updated table through field calculator: PRINCIPAL **see below for description of field and calculation PHONE LOW_GRADE HIGH_GRADE PROGRAMS **see below for description of field and calculation MAGNETINFO **see below for description of field and calculation TYPE **see below for description of field and calculation
-Joined gc_schools and NCES schools based on FEDERAL_ID -Updated: STTCH_RT (in NCES table: STUDENT_TE) TEACHER (in NCES table: TEACHERS_) ENROLLMENT (in NCES table: STUDENTS_) TITLE1SCHO (in NCES table: TITLE_1_SC) FREE_LUNCH REDUCED_LUNCH (in NCES table: REDUCED_LU)
-If school did not have a STATE_ID, then HIGH_GRADE, LOW_GRADE, MAGNETINFO, PROGRAMS (charter school status) were obtained from NCES public schools records by joining on FEDERAL_ID
-For records in gc_school_may12 that were not joined, COMMENT field includes note "NO NCES 09-10 UDPATE"

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GeoPlan process steps of public and private schools in 2017:
The following data sources were used to update the public and private schools data set:
(1) FDOE Public Schools Source: Master School ID 2016-2017 http://doeweb-prd.doe.state.fl.us/EDS/MasterSchoolID Downloaded on 02/20/2017.
(2) FDOE K-12 Private Schools Source: Florida Department of Education K-12 Private Schools Annual Survey 2014-2015 http://www.floridaschoolchoice.org/information/PrivateSchoolDirectory/Default.aspx Downloaded on 02/20/2017
(3) NCES Public Schools CCD Public school data 2014-2015, 2015-2016 school years http://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/ * The directory information on school name, address, and phone number are preliminary data from initial submissions of school level data for 2015-2016. ** Data provided on student membership and staffing are from the official school level data for 2014-2015. Downloaded on 02/20/2017
(4) NCES Private Schools Source: PSS Private School Universe Survey data for the 2013-2014 school year http://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/ Downloaded on 02/20/2017
(5) NCES Colleges Source: College Navigator consisting of 2015-2016 data from the Integrated Postsecondary Education Data System (IPEDS), the core postsecondary education data collection program for NCES. http://nces.ed.gov/collegenavigator/ Downloaded on 04/14/2017
(6) FDOE Florida Colleges Source: Florida Department of Education College System Campuses http://data.fldoe.org/workforce/contacts/default.cfm?action=showList&ListID=11 Accessed on 04/14/2017
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Using schools data sets downloaded from the websites listed above, records were reviewed and edited to apply any available spatial and attribute updates. In most cases, school locations were checked using imagery and Google Street View and either marked as Verified or Not Verified in the FLAG field, please see the FLAG field Attribute Definition for more information.
During the Spatial and Tabular QAQC duplicates and non-qualified points were removed.
The final Point layer was spatially joined to a 2015 statewide parcel layer, and the GCID field was populated with a crosswalk ID linking each point feature with it's corresponding polygon layer feature, GC_SCHOOLSBND_SEP17. The GCID field replaces the SCHOOL_ID field of the previous gc_schools layer as the unique crosswalk ID.
Finally, the GeoPlan Center performed the following attribute table adjustments:
Populated and cleaned all fields.
Fields added include: -GCID: replaces SCHOOLID as unique ID field -FSOURCE -DATASOURCE: replaces SOURCE -MGRS: replaces USNG_FL_1K field
Fields removed include: - COMMON_USE - USE - ACTIVITY
School services/programs from new datasets above that were located at county school district offices (for example:county student services, migrant programs, virtual programs, Mckay scholarship programs, homebound programs, etc.) were not added in order to avoid duplicate points at county school district locations. Schools or programs located at detention centers were not added with this latest update.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Attribute table updates by data source:
For public schools (OP_CLASS = PUBLIC):
(1) Joined GC_SCHOOLS and MSID Schools based on STATE_ID
PRINCIPAL **see below for description of field and calculation PHONE LOW_GRADE **see below for description of field and calculation HIGH_GRADE **see below for description of field and calculation PROGRAMS **see below for description of field and calculation OP_CLASS (For charter schools) **see below for description of field and calculation MAGNETINFO **see below for description of field and calculation TYPE **see below for description of field and calculation
(2) Joined GC_SCHOOLS and NCES Public Schools based on FEDERAL_ID
STTCH_RT (NCES: STUDENT_TEACHER_RATIO) TEACHER (NCES: TEACHERS) ENROLLMENT (NCES: STUDENTS) TITLE1SCHO (NCES: TITLE_1_SCHOOL) FREE_LUNCH (NCES: FREE_LUNCH) REDUCED_LUNCH (NCES: REDUCED_LUNCH)
For schools with no STATE_ID, HIGH_GRADE, LOW_GRADE, MAGNETINFO, were obtained from NCES Public Schools.
For private schools (OP_CLASS = PRIVATE):
(3) Joined GC_SCHOOLS and FDOE Private Schools based on STATE_ID
PRINCIPAL (in NCES: DIRECTOR) PHONE GRADE (in NCES: GRAD_LEVEL)
(4) Joined GC_SCHOOLS and NCES Private Schools based on FEDERAL_ID
LOW_GRADE (in NCES: LOGRADE) **see below for description of field and calculation HIGH_GRADE (in NCES: HIGRADE) **see below for description of field and calculation PHONE (in NCES: PSS_PHONE) ENROLLMENT (in NCES: PSS_ENROLL_T) STTCH_RT (in NCES: PSS_STDTCH) TEACHER (in NCES: PSS_FTE_TEACH)
If school did not have a STATE_ID, then HIGH_GRADE and LOW_GRADE were obtained from NCES records.
